President Biden has nominated Dr. Philip Jefferson for Vice Chair and Dr. Adriana Kugler as a Member on the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. He will also renominate Dr. Lisa Cook for an additional full term as a Member. These nominees have extensive expertise in economics and a focus on pursuing maximum employment and maintaining price stability. The nominations have been met with praise and support from various lawmakers and organizations, who highlight the historic nature of Dr. Kugler's nomination as the first Latina to serve on the Board. They believe that these nominees will contribute to the strong economic recovery under President Biden's administration and ensure diverse representation in decision-making processes.